&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPANY OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ThreatLocker® is a global cybersecurity leader, providing enterprise-level cybersecurity tools for the Managed Services Provider (MSP) industry to improve the security of servers and endpoints. ThreatLocker’s combined Application Whitelisting, Ringfencing™, Storage Control and Privileged Access Management solutions are leading the cybersecurity market towards a more secure approach of blocking unknown application vulnerabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ThreatLocker’s Account Manager will drive retention and growth amongst our clientele. The ideal candidate will have the ability to identify and understand business needs, and provide viable solutions to our customer base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(26, 113, 200);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role will be based in Dubai and is an in-office position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SCOPE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ThreatLocker&#39;s Account Manager is responsible for, but not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with the Account Executive and internal team,&amp;nbsp;interfacing with&amp;nbsp;clients and partner agencies to ensure projects are on target with&amp;nbsp;objectives, budget, and schedule.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Establishing and&amp;nbsp;maintaining&amp;nbsp;a direct relationship with the client and partner agencies through monthly or quarterly meetings.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating client communications relating to purpose, rationale, needs, and due dates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting in&amp;nbsp;the pre-sales cycle in deployment&amp;nbsp;of and&amp;nbsp;securing agents and/or licenses&amp;nbsp;purchased&amp;nbsp;by clients. Leading communications efforts with Solution Engineers on reporting on secured licenses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiating and managing processes related to pricing, invoicing, and budgets, to obtain approvals. Supporting the team in developing new or renewal contracts, and relaying changes to&amp;nbsp;appropriate stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting Account Executive in developing strategic proposals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with Operations and Sales on managing the relationship, issues, and questions of clients/partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tracking client/partner metrics to understand their success, issues, and growth opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travelling&amp;nbsp;accross&amp;nbsp;target GCC Markets to meet with customers,&amp;nbsp;acquire&amp;nbsp;feedback on partnership success,&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;strong&amp;nbsp;relationships&amp;nbsp;and discuss&amp;nbsp;product&amp;nbsp;expansion within accounts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consulting with clientele on product updates and&amp;nbsp;features, and&amp;nbsp;training appropriately.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as an ambassador of&amp;nbsp;ThreatLocker’s&amp;nbsp;mission, brand, and product.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalating customer issues through technical channels,&amp;nbsp;management,&amp;nbsp;and other avenues to ensure issue resolution is reached.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arabic Speaking is Mandatory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of experience in account management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Suite applications (i.e.&amp;nbsp;Excel, Word, PowerPoint)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to manage and direct resources to aid client in achieving its marketing&amp;nbsp;objectives, while managing a budget and timeline&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management skills with the ability to manage multiple programs simultaneously.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills

